-- Booz Allen Among 17 Winners of $6 Billion Cybersecurity Award
-- B y   C h r i s   S t r o h m   a n d   D a n i e l l e   I v o r y
-- 2013-08-13T16:38:29Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-08-13/booz-allen-among-17-winners-of-6-billion-cybersecurity-award.html
Booz Allen Hamilton Holding Corp. (BAH) 
and  Lockheed Martin Corp. (LMT)  are among 17 winners of a $6 billion
U.S. contract that will create a shopping hub for government
agencies seeking to shield their  computer networks  from hackers.  General Dynamics Corp. (GD) ,  Computer Sciences Corp. (CSC) ,  Northrop
Grumman Corp. (NOC)  and  SAIC Inc. (SAI)  also were awarded seats on the
Department of Homeland Security contract, part of what may
become the biggest unclassified cybersecurity program in the
federal government. The U.S. General Services Administration
announced the awards today.  The contracts are valued at as much as $6 billion during as
many as five years.  The companies will provide central hubs in which local,
state and federal agencies can buy computer hardware and
software as well as consulting services to help manage
employees’ access to networks, according to the government’s
Dec. 10 request for bids.  Other winners include  Dynamics Research Corp. (DRCO) , ManTech
International Corp.,  Hewlett-Packard Co. (HPQ)  and  International
Business Machines Corp. (IBM) , SRA International Inc. and  Kratos
Defense & Security Solutions Inc. (KTOS)   To contact the reporters on this story:
